NAME
    csvtomd - Convert CSV files to Markdown tables

SYNOPSIS
    csvtomd [options] [FILE]

DESCRIPTION
    csvtomd is a command-line tool that converts CSV (Comma-Separated Values) files to Markdown-formatted tables. It reads CSV data from a file or standard input and outputs a nicely formatted Markdown table.

OPTIONS
    -h, --help            Show this help message and exit
    -v, --version         Show program's version number and exit
    -i DELIMITER, --input-delimiter DELIMITER
                          Input delimiter (default: ,)
    -o DELIMITER, --output-delimiter DELIMITER
                          Output delimiter (default: |)
    -p, --padding         Pad the content of the cells (default: False)
    -n, --no-header       Specify that the CSV doesn't contain a header row
    --padding-width WIDTH
                          Width of cell padding (default: 1)
    --table-width WIDTH   Width of table (default: 0 for no maximum)
    -q, --quoting         Enable quoting for CSV parsing (default: False)

USAGE
    csvtomd [options] input.csv > output.md
    cat input.csv | csvtomd [options] > output.md

EXAMPLES
    csvtomd data.csv > table.md
    csvtomd -i ';' -p data.csv > table.md
    cat data.csv | csvtomd --no-header > table.md

OUTPUT
    The command outputs a Markdown-formatted table to stdout.

BREAKDOWN
csvtomd is a Python script. It:
1. Reads CSV data from a file or stdin
2. Parses the CSV data
3. Formats the data into a Markdown table
4. Outputs the Markdown table to stdout
